results.content: The work is structured into four parts: a brief presentation of the company; an external and internal analysis to identify its strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats; an economic-financial analysis that forms the core of the study; and a final section with the main conclusions and limitations. To achieve this, several phases were involved, such as: identifying the communication and positioning challenges faced by companies with a sustainable focus in the city in question; analyzing the conceptual foundations of the circular economy and its link to sustainable marketing, integrating theoretical contributions from relevant authors; studying successful sustainable marketing experiences and extracting lessons applicable to the local context; developing a business model based on the Business Model Canvas, which contemplates an efficient organizational structure, a differentiated value proposition, and a sustainability-oriented service approach; establishing circularity strategies applied to marketing, adapted to the characteristics of local SMEs; and evaluating the commercial, technical, economic, and financial viability of the proposed venture.
